evaluation.response:
Taking care of others is no easy task. While taking care of others it is necessary to take care of oneself. Constantly balancing a work life, personal life, and taking care of others can be exhausting.

It can be really tough to manage all that, on top of your own work responsibilities. Juggling multiple tasks at once, while caring for mom, is more than just stating the obvious. It can lead to burnout.&#x20;

People often underestimate the toll helping others can take on one self. It cannot be overstated the importance of prioritizing mental health and finding resources for support. There's great value in asking for help when you need it.

It's okay that you're struggling with these thoughts. They can be overwhelming and feel very scary. It takes courage to acknowledge and share them, even here. One of the best ways to rid unwanted thoughts when one feels too quiet is to start speaking again. This can be as simple as talking to one of your neighbors.

Letting yourself know that these thoughts aren't invincible and that there are people and resources who care about you and want to support you is another too.&#x20;

The National Suicide Prevention Lifeline has many resources available to you if you are having thoughts of suicide or self harm. It is always okay to ask for help. In fact, staying safe and reacting quickly are two key factors when one is having unwanted thoughts.
